text: The Kallakoopah Creek, part of the Lake Eyre basin, is a watercourse located in the southern part of the Simpson Desert in the Australian state of South Australia. It is an anabranch of Warburton Creek. ==See also== *List of rivers of South Australia ==References== Category:Rivers of South Australia Category:Lake Eyre basin Category:Far North (South Australia)
title: Kallakoopah Creek
